This paper talks about three things about Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, it gives a short meaning of the problem. Next, it talks about how to find out if someone has CAPD. Finally, it shows how a teacher can help a student with CAPD in a regular classroom.

Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD) or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) is when the brain does not use sound information well. It means the brain has trouble taking in sounds and making sense of them. People with CAPD can hear sounds, but their brain has trouble understanding them. The part of the brain that changes sounds into words and tells the difference between sounds does not work well. 

The first time people talked about this type of problem was in the 1950s. They called it “auditory imperception.”  Doctors started testing children with problems talking. In 1954, doctors in Italy started making tests for these children. In 1961, a doctor named Kimura made a test to see how the brain hears sounds. In 1977, a big meeting talked about this problem and made more doctors want to study it.

CAPD can show up in many ways. A person with CAPD may have trouble hearing sounds in space, telling sounds apart, or recognizing sound patterns. They may have trouble understanding sarcasm or telling when someone is speaking quickly. Sometimes they may miss sounds if another sound comes right after it. They may also have trouble understanding sounds that are said together.

To find out if someone has CAPD, a doctor will ask them questions and watch how they listen. They may also use tests to see how well they hear. There is no one test that always works, and doctors do not know what causes CAPD. Some tests use many sounds at once and ask the person to tell the difference between them. Other tests record sounds in the ear and see how the brain reacts.

The play Twelfth Night say that disguise good for trick people. But, in the end, a person must stop the disguise. If not, they lose them self.  Ending a trick is hard. People may be mad. So, a person must choose: stay safe, or keep friends. Some people not care if tricked. Other people angry. 

Disguise as a man or woman is hard. Why do people do it? Viola do it to be safe. She say: “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)
Viola new in a new place. She pretend to be a man to stay safe. Her plan work, but she lose friends. She can’t be close with women. Also, Olivia think Viola is a man and fall in love. Olivia say: “Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138) Viola also like Orsino. Orsino say: “Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)



Twelfth Night show how trick can help people see their real feelings. Olivia and Orsino may have feelings they hide. Viola help them see. Is Olivia like Cesario because he man? Or does she like women? Maybe Olivia just judge people by looks. She like Cesario, then like Sebastian. She see Viola as a sister, not a love. She say: “A sister, you are she.” (5.1.315)

German rule in Africa was bad. Some people say it was very bad. This is true for the Ovaherero and Nama people in South West Africa. Germany hurt these people a lot.  But not all of German Africa was like this.  Germany ruled many places in Africa. Each place was different.  The way Germany taught people to read and write was different too.

When Britain took over German East Africa, they saw many Africans who could read and write. Germany had good schools in Kamerun and other places.  But in South West Africa, things were different.  The German government did not help teach Africans to read and write. Instead, they let churches teach the children.  Germany did help teach Europeans in South West Africa to read and write.

This made a big difference. In other German places, many Africans were educated. In South West Africa, most people could not read or write.

Why was this different? This paper will talk about the reasons why. We will look at what the settlers and the people who ruled South West Africa thought about Africans. 

There are many books about how Germany taught people in Africa.  Most of these books are in German and are old. They talk about the schools in each place. Later books, in English, compared schools in different places.  One book talks about South West Africa and East Africa. This book says that the many settlers in South West Africa are one reason why schools were different there.

South West Africa was a good place to live for Europeans. It was not as hot as some other places. There were many Europeans in South West Africa, more than in any other place except East Africa.

Popular music has many kinds.  Many of these kinds have smaller kinds.  Rock, rap, country, jazz, and folk are some big kinds. Heavy metal is one big kind that has many smaller kinds. Heavy metal music is very strong and loud. It talks about dark feelings. People like heavy metal because it is different and exciting.  

Heavy metal started a long time ago. Now there are so many different kinds that it is hard to know what heavy metal is. It uses sounds from other kinds of music. To know heavy metal, we need to know how it started. 

Heavy metal is a movement, not just a kind of music. It is about darkness. Heavy metal music is loud, fast, and exciting. The people who play it are good musicians. Heavy metal also started when people used drugs.

In the 1970s, many people used drugs. This made music different and strange. Heavy metal music is dark and strong, like the music from a long time ago called Romantic music. One example is the song "Helter Skelter" by the Beatles. This song is loud and fast. It is about using drugs.

Many years before the artists of the Surrealist movement started to paint their strange pictures, the artist Henri Rousseau was making his own dreams, both real and imagined. His painting, "The Dream," from the year 1910, shows not only a woman amazed by the things she sees in her dream, but also Rousseau's own hopes and wishes as a painter.  He always wanted people to see and like his art. He wanted to be famous. But he had a hard choice to make. 

To be accepted by the art world, he could copy the styles that were popular. Or he could paint in his own way, even if it was different. "The Dream" is his best painting that shows this fight inside him. 

To understand "The Dream," we need to know about Rousseau's life. He was born on May 21, 1844, in Laval, France. His father was a successful businessman. Rousseau did not learn to paint in school. He worked for the government for many years. He was a collector of taxes. He had a wife and children, but they all died. He was very sad. He started to paint to find comfort. 

Unlike other painters who painted about simple country life, Rousseau painted about the things he saw every day. He wanted to be accepted by the art world, but it was hard. He did not start to become famous until other artists, like Matisse, were already well known.

Many thinkers say that ethics and art are close. They say that truth and beauty are the same. I agree. Like John Keats said, “Beauty is truth, truth beauty- That is all / Ye know on earth, and all ye need to know.” We learn many things in school and life. But we learn about good and beauty in a different way.  We do not need to be taught. Both ethics and art try to show us what is good and beautiful, not tell us how to be good or make beautiful things. We try to explain why art is good or why an action is right. But we can never fully say why something is good or beautiful.  If you ask someone about their favorite art, they will say, “There's just something about it.”  Art and morals are more than just their parts. Like Flannery O'Connor said, “A story is a way to say something that can't be said any other way . . . you tell a story because a statement would be inadequate.” We can talk about art, but there is something more that we feel. Ethics is the same.  Wittgenstein said, “Ethics cannot be expressed. / Ethics is transcendental.” This “something” that we feel is what makes art and morals so powerful. They are both special.
Ethics and art touch us in a deep way. We feel them, but we cannot always explain them. Literature is especially close to ethics. McKean said, “What most distinguishes literature from the other arts, what is, in truth, unique about the art, is its moral quality. It may be that moral standards are inappropriate to other arts, music, for instance, but they seem to be as relevant to literature as they are to life itself. Living necessarily involves values. . . . Literature is important to us precisely because of the values we find there” .

Germany is a strong country today. It has a strong culture. This culture is found in many places, from München to Kiel.  You can see it in Köln and Dresden too. Germany's culture is unique because it comes from many different groups of people.

The land where Germany is now is called Germania. People do not know for sure where the name came from.

One writer, Tacitus, said the name came from a group of people called the Tungrians. He said they were called Germans before they crossed the Rhine River to fight the Gauls. Julius Caesar used the word "Germanus" in his writings about fighting the Gauls. He used it to talk about the people he had not conquered. Some people think the word came from the Gauls. They may have used it to talk about people who lived near them.

Caesar wrote: "The Germans, who dwell beyond the Rhine, with whom they (the Gauls) are continually waging war.....They contend with the Germans in almost daily battles."

Other people think the name came from a weapon the Germans used, called a ger, or from an old Irish word meaning "to shout."

The Roman writer Tacitus wrote about the Germans in 98 AD. He said he thought the Germans were original people. He said they did not mix with other people.

The Romans did not want to live in Germania. They fought with the Germans sometimes, but mostly they stayed in their own empire. The Germans traded with the Romans and some even served in the Roman army.

I look down. My mind sees the thing in front of me. I look at it without feeling. I think about it, but my thoughts go in and out fast. My mind is working well. It is like a river, moving smoothly.

Once, an artist told me to get a book. The book is called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain." I want to learn to draw. I want to do this since I was six years old. The book teaches how to draw. It teaches how the brain sees lines.

The book says to draw a square around a picture. This makes a big picture easy to see. For example, a bowl of fruit on a table in a kitchen is easy to see if it is just the bowl.

I look at the bowl in front of me. I cannot see the square. I am amazed. Great artists have had famous styles. Picasso had a blue time. Monet liked green. Italian artists used many colors.

I think this is my start. My art will be brown.

I touch the thing I will use to draw. My hand moves. My mind makes the hand move. This could be a big moment for me.

Water moves. It is calm and clear. Things break off and go away.

My hand moves again. It is faster now. I hit the handle of the toilet.

The brown thing will not go away. It is stuck.

I hold a mop. I am wearing a tie. I look at the brown thing. Someone put it there. It is a message for the people who clean the bathroom.

I flush the toilet again. I think about it. Then I go to the toilet paper. I wrap it around my hand. I look like I am wearing an oven mitt.

I stand up. I bend down. I put my hand in the bowl.

Teenage drivers are dying in crashes. Many things make this a big problem. The National Institutes of Health say teen brains are not ready for driving. Teens also have little driving experience. This leads to more accidents, crashes, and speeding.

Teens are in more danger when they drive with friends. Everyone knows teens like to drive with friends. A study in California shows the risk goes up with the number of friends in the car.

Some states try to help by giving teens special licenses. These licenses limit driving time and the number of passengers. But these are not good enough. Teens, as a group, are not ready to drive safely.

Doctor Marvin Zuckerman says 18 is too young to drive. He says young people want to take risks for fun. This risk-taking makes them bad drivers. It is better to wait until teens are older and calmer.

If we keep giving licenses to young teens, there will be more deaths. By 2010, many more teen drivers will be on the road.

There is a simple way to fix this. Schools can teach driver’s education, but no one under 18 can drive. Teens can get a permit before a full license. They also need to practice driving with an adult.

The number of practice hours should be the same everywhere. In California, teens need 6 hours of driving lessons and 50 hours of practice.  This would make sure all teens are ready to drive safely. This will help save lives.

I look at old movies from the Library of Congress. I watch many movies with tricks, fifteen from nineteen ninety-five to nineteen zero-one. These movies use editing to make magic. I look at how the movies are made and how some are different.

Most trick movies are made inside. The camera does not move. The actors move back and forth. They do not walk towards or away from the camera. In the movie “Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel”, the actors move left and right. 

The movies use long shots. The camera does not get close to the actors. This is like the theater. People see the whole stage.

Most trick movies are short. They are one idea. They are like tricks, magic, and disappearing acts.

One movie is called “The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots”. It looks like one shot, but it is many shots put together.

John Taylor was a strong supporter of Republican ideas. He was a farmer, but he also worked in government for a short time. People knew him for his strong beliefs about freedom and government. He believed that farming was the best job. This belief influenced his ideas about how the government should work. 

John Taylor thought that America had a chance to create a perfect government. There were no old ways to get in the way. He believed people had natural rights that were important and connected. If one right was taken away, all rights were weaker. The government should not control these rights.

Taylor thought a good government should understand that people are good and bad. He believed that good government protects private property, helps farming, and does not let businesses get too powerful. He thought a good government would be fair, even if the people running it were selfish. He believed people are always looking out for themselves, but this is not bad unless it hurts other people. A good government keeps people from doing bad things.

Taylor wanted the government to follow the Constitution very closely. He wanted a small government with only the powers given to it in the Constitution. He thought a big government was expensive and could be unfair. He also thought it was important to understand what the people who wrote the Constitution meant, not just read the words. He thought the Declaration of Independence was more important than the Constitution because it said America was made of separate states, not one big country.

Figure 17 shows a big drop in commuter logs in the third month of the project. This was sad. We do not know why this happened. In winter, fewer people bike or walk to campus. This may be why some logs were not filled out. December is also the end of the fall semester. Everyone is busy with schoolwork and grades. Filling out logs may have been forgotten. December is also the start of the holidays. Students and teachers have a long break. Many people do not come to campus. Classes begin again in late January. This may also explain the low number of logs in January. But this does not explain the low number in February. 

It is possible that projects have a lot of energy at first, and then the energy goes down. To stop this, we had Carpool Challenge Week in March. This was a special event to make people use the logs again. It worked and more people used the logs. One problem was keeping people using the project. This is hard because of holidays and school breaks. Another problem is that people like driving their cars. It is part of our culture. We need to give people good reasons to use other ways to get to school. We gave out prizes like gift cards. We gave them to local places like restaurants, coffee shops, and stores. It would be interesting to see if bigger prizes, like a bike, hybrid car, or electric car, would have worked better. Not changing the prizes was a problem. If we had better prizes, more people might have used the logs.

An ETF is a type of investment that tries to match the price of an index, a group of things like gold or oil, or a basket of things like many stocks.  It is like an index fund, but more flexible and can be bought and sold on an exchange like a single stock. 

ETFs have the benefits of index funds and single stocks. They can be traded easily, and you can buy or sell small amounts.  ETFs also cost less than most mutual funds. But, you have to pay a fee each time you buy or sell an ETF, just like with stocks.

ETFs come in many types. 

It is good for smart investors to check if the benefits of an ETF, like having many different investments, are real and how well they work.  

For this example, we will look at an ETF called IHF. We will compare it to the ten most important stocks in the ETF to see if owning the ETF is better than owning those ten stocks. We will also look to see if there are better ways to invest in those ten stocks that would give a better return.

To make things easier, we will only look at the ten most important stocks in IHF, which own 63.58% of the ETF.

We can use the current amount of money each stock has in the ETF to see how well those ten stocks represent the whole ETF.  This will help us see how much each stock adds to the risk and return of the ETF if we owned all ten stocks in the same amounts.

The chart below shows the return and risk of a portfolio made up only of the top ten stocks compared to the whole ETF. 

The chart shows that a portfolio of just the top ten stocks could give a higher return with less risk than the whole ETF. But, there is a chance that the difference may not be important.


To know for sure if the difference is important, we need to look at the risk of each stock.

Dream-Land is one of Edgar Allan Poe’s good poems. In “Dream-Land,” Poe use the word “Thulé” in lines 6 and 56. A man named Mabbott said the word comes from Virgil. Virgil used it for an island north of Britain. The Greeks thought this island was the end of the known world.

It is true that Virgil used the word. But there is a more modern source that is important. Poe liked German writers.

One quote shows Poe knew about Goethe’s writing. A man named Karl J. Arndt wrote a book about Poe and Goethe. He says Poe copied Goethe’s poem.

The Oxford Companion to English Literature says Goethe wrote the famous play *Faust*. It was made in two parts. The first part came out in 1808, and the second part came out in 1832 when Goethe died.

There is a short poem in the second part of *Faust*. It is called “The King of Thulé.”  The poem is about a king whose wife dies. He gets a cup from her as a gift. After his wife dies, he drinks a lot and cries for her. He decides to die. He gives his things to his children, but he keeps the cup. He goes to a cliff, throws the cup in the ocean, closes his eyes, and dies. The king in “The King of Thulé” is like a dark copy of Poe’s sadness and his drinking.

*Faust* was made into a play in 1842. That was less than a year before Poe used the word “Thulé” in “The Pit and the Pendulum.”

Poe uses “Thulé” twice in his writing. He uses “ultma Thule” in “The Pit and the Pendulum,” but he uses “Thulé” twice in “Dream-Land.” “The King of Thulé” and “Dream-Land” can be read together. In “Dream-Land,” the speaker describes the land of Thulé. It is dark and lonely. He is with dead friends. He sees a world without color. These things are like what happens in “The King of Thulé.” The speaker in “Dream-Land” feels like he is in Goethe’s poem.

Goethe was a very important writer. Poe would have known him. Poe said he liked Tennyson. Because Poe liked Tennyson, he would have known Goethe.

A person who is hurt in a store can get extra money. This extra money is called "punitive damages". To get this money, the person must show the store acted badly.

A judge will look at if a customer, Jennifer Palmer, can get extra money for an injury. She fell on spilled applesauce in a store.

The store manager knew about the spill. He was told twice, but he did not clean it up for half an hour. He said he was eating dinner.  

Jennifer Palmer's lawyer can say the manager should have known the spill was dangerous. Other people had fallen on spills in the store before.

The lawyer can also say the manager acted badly.  Six people fell in the store that year, and he still did not clean up spills.

On October 13, 2009, two workers told the manager there was a spill. He said he was busy.

At 5:30 pm, Jennifer Palmer fell and hurt her back.

In California, a person can get extra money if the store did something very wrong.

The manager knew the spill was dangerous. He did not care if someone got hurt.

Four years ago I took a class about Islam at CBC. We talked a lot about if Islam is a bad religion. I think this is more important now than ever.

The news has changed how it talks about Islam since 9/11. At first, it was very bad. Now it is very good. I do not think we could have had a president like Barack Obama, who has Muslim family, in 2001.

I am interested in the story of Muhammad.  I thought Muhammad forced people to be Muslim. He would fight tribes and make them join his religion. But his story says he was a good man. People misunderstood him, and he was kind. People liked his ideas and joined him.

Some things about his life are like Jesus. Like when he made food for many people with just a little bit. The story makes Muhammad seem like a good man who did not need to prove anything. This is bad because it makes Jesus less important. It is like they are copying Jesus.

There are many stories about people who joined Islam. But the stories are not always told by people who saw it happen. They are told by people who heard it from someone else. This makes the stories less believable.

I think the worst thing is that the story makes Muhammad seem like a perfect man. But history says he was not. I wonder if Muslims know the real story about Muhammad.

Jesus' teachings changed the world.  But after he died, people changed what his teachings meant.  We can see this change over time.  Christianity changed a lot from its start.  Today, the world is changing fast.  New ideas are popular.  Some people like old ideas.  They do not want to change.  But maybe they are not important enough to change everything.  In the future, more Christians will want to understand the true teachings of Jesus.  They will want to know what Jesus really said, not what was added later.  It will take a long time, but people will go back to Jesus' original ideas.  They will remove the changes that happened over time.

This change will happen slowly, like a clock going backward.  People will go back to how Jesus taught.  The big change will start in America and Europe.  Many people will follow Jesus' ideas.  The church will be strong.  But Christianity will become more the same.  There will be less difference between groups of Christians.

History shows us big changes can happen.  For example, Christians were hated a long time ago, but then the Roman Empire became Christian.  America changed from slavery to African-Americans leading the country.  Now, Christianity will change again.  It will go back to its start.  People will find the original teachings of Jesus.

To make this happen, people will read Jesus' words in a new way.  They will see them as symbols, not just words.

What happened since Jesus' time?  Long ago, Judaism was the start of Christianity.  Judaism has one God.  People believe God gave them laws.  The Jewish people had many groups:  Sadducees, Pharisees, Essenes, Zealots, and many others.

The book "The Jungle" shows that people can be very greedy. They only want good things for themself. They do not care about others.  The book shows this with the people who own the big factories. They only want their factories to be big and strong. They do not care if people get hurt. Upton Sinclair writes, "The line of the buildings stood clear-cut and black against the sky; here and there out of the mass rose the great chimneys, with the river of smoke streaming away to the end of the world". This shows that the factory owners do not care about pollution. They do not care if people or animals are hurt.

The factory owners also do not care about the people who work for them. They want to make more money. They make workers work for long hours. Sometimes they fire many workers without warning. There were not many laws to protect workers at that time. This means the factory owners could do bad things.

The workers were treated very badly.  They had to work in bad conditions. They did not have money or help when they were fired. Some people say the workers were like slaves. Sinclair writes, "Here is a population, low-class and mostly foreign, hanging always on the verge of starvation and dependent for its opportunities of life upon the whim of men every bit as brutal and unscrupulous as the old-time slave drivers; under such circumstances, immorality is exactly as inevitable, and as prevalent, as it is under the system of chattel slavery."

Many writers use special ways to make readers feel a certain way about important things. Some ways work better than others.  F. Scott Fitzgerald uses many ways to do this in his book The Great Gatsby. Sometimes, he uses words that do not usually go together. This gives readers a special feeling about a subject. Other times, he gives a meaning to a symbol and uses it this way.

Fitzgerald uses this last way with many colors, like gold, green, white, gray, and red and pink. In his book, he builds up meaning for these colors. Then, he uses the meaning to make readers think of a feeling about something important.

Fitzgerald uses white and gray to mean the same thing: being the same. White is a bit nicer and classier. Gray is older and faded. He shows this meaning at the start of the story. Daisy and Jordan always wear white. Everyone at Gatsby's party wears white too. Nick wears white clothes, Tom wears a white shirt, and Catherine is pale white. The only time people are not in white is when Nick sees Gatsby’s party. “The halls are colorful with bright colors” (40). Fitzgerald shows these colors in simple things too. Nick goes to work in “white streets” (56). Nick sees “gray names” (61) of people at Gatsby’s party. Catherine lives in a building that is like a “white cake” (28). He also describes common people or places as white or gray. Jordan and Daisy had a white childhood. There are gray cars and gray land in the valley of ashes. The Italian child on the train is gray.

After Fitzgerald uses these colors a lot, he uses them to show that something is not important or special. He does this with Daisy. After a long time without using these colors, Fitzgerald describes Daisy in white. Readers see Daisy as less of a person and more like something that Gatsby wants. He uses these colors around Daisy to make her seem like a part of something uniform.

San Diego is good for growing food. The weather is warm and sunny. Farmers grow many things like tomatoes, oranges, lettuce, squash, broccoli, herbs, peaches, lemons, berries, honey, and peppers.

Many people in San Diego want to buy food that is grown without chemicals. There are many groups that sell food this way. These groups have long lists of people who want to join. People also like to buy eggs and milk that are organic. Many organic farms let people visit and see how they grow food. They also let people walk and watch birds. This is good for the farmer because they can make money and teach people about farming.

Farming without chemicals is good for plants and animals because it does not hurt the soil or water. But, it is harder to grow food this way. It takes more work to keep away bugs and weeds. It also costs more money.


The land is near a town called Potrero. It is a mix of plants like chaparral, grass, and oak trees. It is next to a big forest called the Cleveland National Forest. This area is important for many animals and plants. Many of them are in danger of disappearing. This area was used by Native Americans for a long time. Then, people used it to raise cows and sell wood.

I looked at land for sale online and found programs that help farmers. I also found an organic farm near this land to see how it works.

Culture is very important in any talk to make a deal.  Culture is hard to explain. It is more about what it is not than what it is. Culture is not the same for everyone. It is not one thing. Saying things like "all Russians are stubborn" or "all Japanese are nice" is not right. While it is good to know some things about a culture, it is more helpful to know how that culture will act at the table. When we meet a new culture, we see it through our own culture.  We make comparisons. 

To understand a new culture, we can learn about its history and its ideas. We should not try to change it. We should just accept it and work with it. This is especially true when we are in a weak position. If we go to a new place, showing respect for its ways can help us make a deal.

Culture is not just about countries. Companies also have their own cultures. Some companies work long hours, others work less. We can see a company's culture in how people dress, how they talk, and who they hire. Some companies encourage helping others, others only help certain groups.  We can see this in American companies. They are different from each other. 

Values are important because they tell us why people act the way they do. If a culture values saving face or being together, a person will not shame their company to win a deal. If a culture values hard work, they will not give up easily.

Before we make a deal, we should learn about the other person's culture. But it is also good to learn about them as a person. This will help us make a good deal.

The thinker tells us, "There is no God."  This idea is in the Bible in the book of Psalms, chapter 14. 

St. Anselm uses this idea to talk about God.  He thinks that people can know God is real by thinking about him. 

He thinks God is so big that we can know he must be real just by thinking about him. We know God is real because we can think about him.

St. Thomas Aquinas had a similar idea. He thinks we can know God is real by looking at the world around us. 

He says that the world changes, things need a cause, things could not always exist, things have different levels of goodness, and the world works well together. He thinks these things mean God must exist.

Both thinkers say that God is real. 

But neither one fully shows us how to know God is real.

Long ago, in the fifth or sixth century BCE, a prince was born. He was to become Buddha. Buddha gave up his life of comfort and found wisdom. His ideas made Buddhism.  The oldest part of Buddhism is called Theravada. Buddhism is very old—over two thousand five hundred years. It looks different now than when Buddha lived.  

We see this in Sri Lanka, a country where Theravada is important. They have a special ceremony every year called the water-cutting ceremony. Monks and regular people do this ceremony. It is a tradition, but Buddha did not teach about it.

Buddhism has changed over time. It changed on the outside and on the inside. This change came from things both good and bad from people who believed in Buddhism and people who did not.

We will use special words to talk about these changes. 

* "Inside" means from people who follow Buddhism. 
* "Outside" means from people who do not follow Buddhism. 
* "Bad" means something that hurts Buddhism.
* "Good" means something that does not try to hurt Buddhism.


We will talk about the main ideas of Theravada Buddhism. Buddhists believe in three things—Buddha, the teachings (Dhamma), and the group of monks (Sangha). The Dhamma means the teachings of Buddha, written in three parts: 

* Sutta Pitaka: Stories about Buddha's life and teachings.
* Vinaya Pitaka: Rules for monks.
* Abhidhamma Pitaka: Thinking about what Buddhism means.

The most important ideas are:

* There is no soul (Anatta).
* Life always has suffering (Dukkha).
* Everything changes (Anicca).

By knowing these, we can stop being reborn over and over (Sansara). We can also stop wanting things (lobha), being angry (dosa), and being confused (moha).  When we understand these things, we become enlightened.

The Vinaya Pitaka has rules for everyone. Regular people follow five rules: No killing, no lying, no stealing, no sex before marriage, and no drinking alcohol. Monks have many more rules. 

The most important idea is the Four Noble Truths:

1. Life has suffering.
2. Suffering comes from wanting things.
3. Suffering can be stopped.
4. There is a way to stop suffering.

The United States and Mexico were like two neighbors who did not like each other very much. This did not like each other for a long time, from 1836 to 1893. The biggest fight was the Mexican-American War. In this war, the United States took land from Mexico.  Many smaller fights happened after that. These fights stopped before World War I.  

The fight started because Americans and Mexicans had different ideas about religion, culture, and how to live. They also wanted different things. This is like other countries that live next to each other. They often have disagreements.

The United States had big problems with Mexico and Cuba. Other countries in Latin America did not have these problems with the United States.

Religion was a big problem. In the past, Americans did not like Catholicism. This made things hard between the United States and Mexico. 

The United States and Mexico fought about land many times. People stole things from each other.  This made both countries send soldiers to the border.  

Finally, the fighting stopped. Mexico needed the United States to help it. The United States wanted to help Mexico make money.

Fifteen years ago, I became sick. I did not know I was sick. I worked as a nurse. I chose this job because I wanted to be safe. I did not feel safe as a child. People told me, "You will always have a job. People always need help." So, even though I wanted to be a scientist or a journalist, I became a nurse.


I was 46 years old and single. I had no money. I could not work. I am still disabled. After 15 years on disability, I have nothing. I get by, but every day is hard. I do not feel safe. I feel bad about myself.

I know this: I could not have made it without my family and friends. They helped me. When bad things happen, you need help.


There will always be problems. We cannot always plan for them. We cannot do everything ourselves. 

I agree that we should not depend on the government too much. It is not working well.

But, I think we need to help each other. We need to trust each other. 

People say that America was built on being independent. But America was built on helping each other.

Be prepared. I am. I have a kit for emergencies. I have food, water, and tools. I know how to use them. But also, get to know your neighbors.

Why do living things change over time? Are there limits to how they change? Even today, scientists have a hard time describing how living things change using math. But, scientists are starting to use math to understand how shells change shape, both during an animal's life and over many generations. Our study uses math to understand how shells change in a group of animals called Prunum. We look at pictures of Prunum shells and use them to create computer models. These models help us see how shells could change in different ways. We also study real Prunum shells to understand how they change. 

A shell is like a tube that moves in a circle. This circle is called a whorl.  Each whorl is like a layer of the shell. There is a line between each whorl called a suture. The biggest whorl is the last one, called the body whorl. The other whorls are called the spire. The tip of the spire is called the apex, and the opposite end is called the base. The animal lives inside the shell and comes out through an opening called the aperture.

We can look at shells from different angles.  The most common way is the apertural view, where the opening is facing us and the tip is pointing up.

To count the whorls, look at the shell from the top. Find the first suture line and draw a line through it. Count the whorls from that line, estimating to the nearest quarter whorl.

We can think of a shell as a series of openings moving through time and space as the animal grows. We can track the path of these openings using math. Once we have a math model, we can change the parameters and see how the shell changes.

Indonesia's baby and mother deaths have not gone down much in the last ten years.  Even though Indonesia is doing well on some goals, like clean water, they are not making fast enough progress on keeping moms and kids healthy.  To meet their goals by 2015, they need to do much better.  This paper will look at why this is happening and why they need to make their health system stronger, not just have special programs.

Indonesia has made progress in having more births with a trained helper.  72% of babies are now born with a helper.  But this helper could be a midwife, not a doctor.  Doctors can help if the birth is hard.  So, this is not good news.  Also, fewer kids with diarrhea are seeing a doctor.  We don't have enough information about care after birth, but it seems like this is a problem too.

C-sections are not common.  Only 4% of babies are born this way.  This is less than it should be.  It is also not equal.  In cities, 7% of babies are born by C-section, but only 2% in the country.  This shows that healthcare is better in cities.

Poor people have a hard time getting to healthcare.  The richest families use healthcare 27% more than the poorest families.  This is because poor people can't afford it.

To make things better, we need to figure out how to get more people access to healthcare. Should Indonesia have special programs or make the whole health system better?

Special programs are easy to understand and quick to see results. But they can take money away from other parts of the health system.  People will only work in areas with more money.  This can harm other areas, like family planning.

Too many programs can make things messy.  They can have the same services and paperwork can be a big problem.

Victorian books are known for being very detailed. They often talk about rich people from that time. Two books that are from this time but are different are "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights." Both of these books have mystery and strange parts, which was not common in books from that time. This helps us understand the characters better and why they do the things they do.

Here is a part from "Oliver Twist":

"Many confusing thoughts came into his mind. He felt like he was still walking between Sikes and Crackit, who were fighting angrily. He could hear their words. Then he looked around and saw he was talking to them. Suddenly, he heard gunshots. People were shouting and there were bright lights everywhere. He felt like someone was taking him away quickly. Through all this, he felt a deep pain that bothered him all the time."

Both of these books use mystery often through dreams or dreamlike states. In "Oliver Twist," these strange things help us see inside Oliver and understand his pain and how he sees the world.

When Oliver is shot, he remembers it again in chapter 28, like a dream. He is trying to get help. This shows that Oliver had no control over what happened to him. He was very hurt, and all his senses were numb. He did not even notice the people who were taking him away. He was in so much pain that he could not even feel surprise. The shooting shows that Oliver has no power over his own life. He cannot control what happens to him, even when his life is in danger. This makes us wonder who is responsible for his bad luck. It does not seem to be his own fault. This shooting shows that Oliver is giving up and accepting his fate. Maybe Fagin is breaking him and making him think this way. Otherwise, Oliver would try to do something to save himself.

Here is a part from "Wuthering Heights":

"The day passed by quickly. There was no real day; it came and went so fast. And then night came. Night was so long and quiet. It felt long because it was so quiet. But it also felt short because it was over so quickly."

A few years ago, I worked in an after school program. I helped students in elementary school. I was good at helping with English and reading. One instructor asked me to help a boy named Adrian. He was in third or fourth grade and had trouble reading. I thought something was wrong. He read some letters well, but others he got wrong. It was very strange. Adrian spoke perfect English, but I knew he was of Latino descent. 

We worked hard, but it was difficult. One day, Adrian's mother came to the program. I was watching a few children while the others were on a field trip. Adrian's mother did not speak English. I only knew a little Spanish. We talked using simple words. Then I understood. Adrian could read, but he did not know the English alphabet well. I don't know if this helped him much, but I hope he is doing better now.

I tell this story to show the problem of language barriers in schools, especially here in California. It shows that things are not always obvious. Even a child who speaks English well can have trouble reading.  I think everyone agrees this is a problem. So what can we do?

For Adrian, the solution was simple: help him learn English reading and the alphabet. But for children who do not speak much English, the solution is harder. There is no one answer. Dual language programs, mainstream immersion, private tutors, and ESL classes all have their place. We need to use all of these things together.

First, dual language programs are a good idea. They help all children, not just those whose first language is Spanish. Studies show that children in these programs do better in school. Some people are afraid of this. They think it wastes money and that most children will not benefit. That is not true.  If we used these programs more often, all children would benefit.

How can we do this? We do not need all teachers to be bilingual. That would be too hard. But we can have bilingual helpers or tutors.

Many people believe in something bigger than them.  Some go to church or temple. Others look inside. Some take the beliefs of their parents. Some do not believe.  Some change their beliefs.  People look for answers about life and death.

My father liked cardinals. We sat on the porch. It rained hard. The rain made a loud sound on the roof.  He looked out at the rain. He looked tired. His hair was thin. He did not look at me. I felt sad. I did not want to talk about how much I would miss him.  I hugged him and sat close.

My father died in December.  He was sick for a long time. The medicine did not help. I did not want to see him die. I wanted to remember him happy. I knew he would not want me to watch him die. I stayed in bed for three days. No one called me.

The Gothic story is old and new at the same time.  It is a mix of very old ideas and new ways of telling stories. This is what Ian Watt said in his book, "The Rise of the Gothic Novel". People have said many things about Gothic stories. Some say they are not good. Others say they are very good because they are scary and exciting. The first Gothic story was "The Castle of Otranto" by Horace Walpole.  He used old ideas from stories and new ideas from modern stories to make something new.  Walpole used old stories and new ways to show things to make a new kind of story. He called it "A Gothic Story."

Gothic stories use ideas from old stories and buildings. They use ideas from medieval times. Even when he wrote "The Castle of Otranto",  people already used the word "Gothic" for many things.  It meant old and not good compared to new things. But the Gothic story was a mix of old and new. It used the old style of stories but in a new way.  This is why Gothic stories are still popular today.

One big idea in Gothic stories is chivalry. Chivalry is about how knights used to be trained. It was important to Gothic writers because it showed what a good knight should be like. They thought that people today were not as good as knights.  Gothic writers liked to show the old world as better. They wanted to make people think about how good people used to be. Walpole wrote "The Castle of Otranto" during a time when things were hard. He thought that people today were not as good as they used to be.

In his story, one character is named Frederic. He is a prince. He has been sad because bad things have happened to him. He is supposed to be dead.

The story uses words that show Frederic is a good knight. He is brave and strong.  His story shows how people used to be better than they are now.

Supply chain management is how we move things. We move things from when a customer wants something, all the way to making the thing and then giving it to the customer.  A man named Keith Oliver made up the name "supply chain management" in nineteen eighty-two. He said it is about planning, doing, and watching over the whole process so customers get what they want fast and in a good way. There are six big parts to a supply chain: making, getting stuff, having enough stuff, where stuff is, moving stuff, and using information.  Business managers use these parts to give good service to customers.

First is making. Making is the start of the supply chain. It is how we make everything. Managers need to know what people want to buy. They look at the market to see what people are asking for. Then, managers decide what to make and how much. They also decide where to make it. They choose the best place to make the things, so they are made well and people are happy. After that, managers plan how much work to do and how to keep the machines working. Making is very important. If we do not plan well, it can cost a lot of time and money. For example, I used to work at Wal-Mart and Target. Both companies have plans for everything. There are plans for how workers look, how to get things from trucks, and more. Plans help things run smoothly.

The second part is getting stuff. This is about making smart choices about how to make things. A company might have many ways to make the same thing. Each way uses different workers, machines, and skills. The manager has to choose the best way for each part of the thing. Sometimes, companies hire other companies to make parts. This is called outsourcing. Companies do this to make things faster, better, and cheaper.

Hitler is alive in Burma, the sign says. Ellen Page, star of the movie Juno, stands alone. She holds a paper sign. The words are written with a marker. Burma is a country in Southeast Asia. It is ruled by a bad group of leaders. They took over in 1962. In 2007, people in Burma protested. Many monks joined the protests. They are called the “Saffron Revolution” because monks wear saffron robes. At first, the government let the monks protest. But then, the government became angry. They hurt the monks and took over their homes.  News reporters were caught and put in jail. One reporter, Kenji Nagai, was killed. The government says 13 people died. But a soldier who left the army says many more people died.

This is not new. Governments have always tried to control people. Long ago, Roman leaders said they were chosen by gods. Japanese leaders are believed to be gods. Our president, George W. Bush, talks to a leader of a group called Stupid People Worldwide.

There are many examples of governments hurting people. In 1989, people in China protested. The government hurt many of them. In Rwanda, people killed many people. Hitler killed many Jewish people.

Duke Ellington is a big name in jazz. He played music for a long time and made his band better and better. He played the piano, but he was best at making music. He wrote songs that were hard and good. He made songs that showed off what each band member could do. He made the music fit together well, and made it sound new. He knew how each person played and how they sounded together. This made his music very good. 

A book about music says Ellington used singing like an instrument. He used a song called "Creole Love Call" to show this. He sang without words to make the music sound different. He also made songs that fit the singers. This song is slow and sad. It has six parts.

The first part has a singer and the woodwind instruments talking back and forth. The singer starts smooth and then gets rougher. The second part has a trumpet that plays softly and goes up and down. The third part has a clarinet playing high notes with a quiet piano. The fourth part has the whole band playing like the first part. The fifth part is loud and exciting. The singer and the woodwinds play high notes. The sixth part is like the first part. The singer uses a rough sound like singing with growls. There is a short part after the song with singing and a trombone.

Ellington used singing to make his music sound different. He did this in other songs too. In "Hot and Bothered," he had a trumpet player and a singer talk back and forth. The trumpet player sounds like he is singing, and the singer sounds like an instrument. In "It Don't Mean a Thing," he used a trombone player to start the song.

She always want something. This want was strong. It start when she was about fourteen, just a teen. It stay when she was seventeen. Now, she want a person, not a thing. But she not like any boys. Some boys like her, try to be nice, but no one good enough. She think about this a lot. She try to find why she feel this way. She think of many ideas, but nothing good. So, she live her life, always asking about her wants.

Her home was usually calm. Her parents were good and quiet. They never fight, and they rarely fight with her. The only time they fight is when she want to be free. She was the daughter of calm people, but she have a big, fun personality. She nice, and people like her.

Today, her home not calm. She walk around, looking for new ideas, when she hear her mom scream. She run to the kitchen, scared. "Mom! What happen?" She see her mom on the floor, hurting. Her mom say "Ow" between breaths. The daughter go to her mom and touch her. "Ouch, sweetie, I need to go to the hospital." The mom say the words fast. The daughter know she hurt bad. "Okay, Mom, where should I take you?" The mom point. The daughter was happy she took classes to make herself strong. She carry her mom to the car, put her down, and drive.

The hospital smell like medicine and sickness. But the daughter not care. She worried about her mom. She rush her mom inside and call for help. Some doctors come and put her mom on a bed. They take her away, and the daughter sit and worry.

Her mom fall off a step stool while trying to get a vase from a high shelf.

This study looked at the link between eating a “Mediterranean Diet” (Med diet) and heart health. The study used a score called “alternate Mediterranean (aMed)” to measure how well people followed the Med diet. The aMed diet is like the Med diet but has more plant foods, like fruits, nuts, whole grains, and beans. It also has more good fats and fish, but less meat and unhealthy fats.

People who ate more like the aMed diet had a lower chance of getting heart disease and stroke. This study looked at many women over many years.  The women filled out forms about what they ate. The researchers looked at how their diet scores and their health changed over time. 

They found that women who ate more like the aMed diet had a lower chance of heart problems.

In the year two thousand seven, America had a big money problem. People lost jobs. Houses lost value. Big companies had big trouble. This problem is still here. We must ask: how did this happen? And how can we stop it?  

The money problem was made by leaders who made bad choices. They pushed banks to give loans to people who could not pay them back. The banks did not have enough money to save themselves. They passed the problem to others.

The problem started in nineteen ninety-nine. President Clinton wanted to be popular. He made it easier for people to get loans. A reporter named Steven Holmes said this would be bad. He said it would be like the money problem in the 1980s.

Many things made the problem worse. New kinds of loans were made. People borrowed too much money. When house prices went down, people could not pay their loans.

The five biggest banks in America had a lot of money tied up in loans. They lost a lot of money. Some banks closed. Others were saved by the government.

Ah, exposition.  That part in your story where you tell the reader important things.  It can be boring if you tell too much.  It can be exciting if you tell just the right amount.  Dr. Merlin knows this well.  She has yelled at her computer many times when she writes too much exposition.

Exposition is like telling the reader a history lesson.  It's not always fun to read.  Good writers show the reader important things instead of just telling them.

For example, imagine a story about a woman.  You are told she met her husband, they got married, and then he died.  That's a lot of information to give all at once!  It would be more interesting if the writer showed you how the woman and her husband felt about each other.

You could see how much he loved her through his actions and words.  You could see how much her life changed because he was in it.  If the writer does this, you will care more about the husband and you will feel sad when he dies.


Exposition can be important, but don't use too much.  Show, don't tell!

I watch two news show from Columbus, Ohio. The first show was NBC 4 this morning (August 13, 2011). The first story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife. They did not give her name. His name was Shad Hostettler. They show a picture of him. He look bad. They talk about the story for two minutes. They say he hurt his wife many times. He is in jail now.

The next story was about a young man, Travis Buyers. He is 18 years old. He was shot in Sharon Woods. He is very sick. No one has been caught. The police are looking. This story was short. I think this is because he is a black man. I have seen this many times. The news talks a lot about white people who are hurt or missing. They do not talk much about black people. 

The next story was about a hole in a helicopter. Someone shot at it with a gun. The police think the bullet was from a rifle. They are offering money for information.

The next story was about the rain. It will rain on Saturday. It will be hot this weekend.

The news also talked about a robbery at a store. A black man robbed the store. He wore a hoodie. He is tall and thin.  They talked a lot about his race.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He was a drug dealer. He sold drugs from Texas to Ohio. He went to jail for many years. They said he got 300 months. That is 25 years. They also said he was Hispanic. I think this was not important to the story.

Brothers have a strong bond. This bond is very strong and cannot be broken. 

The bond between brothers has many feelings: love, pride, jealousy, and bad feelings, to name some. Brothers understand each other more than anyone else. They can see themselves when they look at their brother. This bond is strongest when things are bad. The true nature of this bond can be good or bad.

When these feelings are clear, they have a big cost. To understand the feelings between brothers, we must understand the bad things that come with them. When a brother can look another brother in the eye and see their own reflection, they see themselves as they really are. Their actions and the results of those actions show their true character.

In "The Scarlet Ibis," two brothers show this theme. They show all the strong feelings that come with it. In a beautiful and colorful place, these two boys go on a journey that will not work. Sad disappointment fights with intense pride in the end. Only one brother lives. The theme is shown through the main character, Doodle, and how he acts. It is also shown through the story teller's point of view. This tells us about the main character's feelings and how he sees the world. Both of these things influence his actions.

Everything the main character does is about pride. From when he and his little brother, Doodle, first go out together, to their final, bad adventure, the main character feels bad about Doodle. He wanted a brother he could teach all his skills, like "holding my breath, running, jumping, or climbing the vines in Old Woman Swamp.” He wanted a brother who could do things with him, like “someone to race to Horsehead Landing…and someone to perch with in the top fork of the great pine behind the barn.” These things are impossible because Doodle is sick. Doodle has a very weak heart, and it is unlikely he will live long. He will probably never do any hard activity. It was hard for the young main character to have his dreams crushed. In fact, he even thought about killing Doodle by putting a pillow over his face. What kind of child would think about killing a baby? But then Doodle smiled at him and the main character felt better.  This shows that he did not really want to hurt his brother. Deep down, he loved him.

The human brain is a very hard thing to understand.  It is like a machine that thinks.  New technology helps us know more about the brain.  People used to think the brain was like a wax tablet, then a piece of paper, then a book.  Now, people think the brain is like a computer. But remember, these are just ideas. They are not perfect.

The brain gets information from our senses. Our eyes, ears, skin, and tongue send signals to the brain. The brain changes these signals. It looks for patterns and makes sense of what we see, hear, smell, taste, and touch.  

For example, if you see a black box on a white background, your brain takes in the colors and shapes. It knows that the black part is different from the white part, and it learns that it is a box. The brain also uses what it already knows to help it understand things faster. If you know that boxes are usually black, your brain will understand it is a box faster.

The brain decides what is important. It can pay attention to some things and ignore others.  You see many things when you look around, but you do not notice every tiny thing. Your brain focuses on the things that are important to you.

The brain stores information. There are different kinds of memory.  We have short-term memory, and we have long-term memory.  We use our short-term memory for a few seconds. We use our long-term memory for much longer. 

People have many ideas about how the brain stores information. Some think it is like a web of ideas.

Aldous Huxley uses his book *Brave New World* to talk about the dangers of new technology and the way money power makes it worse. The book shows a world where people think the group is more important than the person. They are taught to want happiness right now, no matter what. The people in this world are like pieces in a game. They are controlled by the World Controller, who makes sure they all think the same way. If you look at the book using the ideas of Marxism, you can see that Huxley worries about how these systems are dangerous. He uses big words from Marxism, like "homogeny" and "reification," to show that his book is a warning about the problems with how money and business worked in his time.

Huxley uses the idea of "false consciousness" from Marxism to show how bad capitalism is. This means that regular people don't know the real way things work with money. They are only interested in getting rich themselves. This is because the people in power control what they think. This is clear in *Brave New World*. The lower classes, like the Deltas and Gammas, don't have any real choices. They are taught to buy things, spend money, and enjoy themselves. This is all controlled by the World Controller.  

The book also shows how power works in groups. The World Controller controls the lower classes, who don't even know they are being controlled.  The upper classes know, but they don't do anything to stop it. The book shows how people in the different groups treat each other. This shows how capitalism hurts people.

In *Brave New World*, people don't have real relationships. The characters don't have deep feelings. Maybe Huxley is saying that technology and capitalism take away people's freedom and ability to be themselves. People don't love each other. They don't feel strong emotions. They only talk about each other's bodies.  Also, each group is happy with its place in the world. This shows how capitalism makes people believe that they are better than others if they buy things, follow the rules, and act like everyone else.

I am a student at University Park. I have been here for two and a half years. I live in a dorm far from the center of campus.  Sometimes it takes me 25 minutes to walk to class. A few years ago, the area where my dorm is was empty. Now there are new buildings and sports fields. The campus is growing, and it is hard to get around.

What is the best way to get around? I think a bike is good. But the campus needs to be better for bikes.

I have a friend who started riding a bike again. He said, “Bikes are good. It is the best way to get around.” Biking is good for your health and it is fast.

I live off campus now. It is far from the center of campus. I bought a bike this year. I can ride to my class in five minutes. It would take me 25 minutes to walk. The road is not always easy to ride on.

I like to walk too, but I am busy.  If I did not have a bike, I would have to walk. Walking to class every day would take too much time.
